title: Prep football: Brainerd 21, Sartell 19
text:
Prep football: Brainerd 21, Sartell 19 TIMES STAFF REPORT 7:49 p.m. CDT October 3, 2015 Sartell (Photo: Times graphic) 
BRAINERD — Sartell quarterback Chris Belling finished with 140 yards passing on 18 completions with two touchdowns in the loss to Brainerd. 
The Sabres scored a late touchdown by John Schmidt with eight minutes left in the fourth quarter, but couldn’t get the lead. 
Schmidt led Sartell on the ground with 57 yards. 
First quarter 
S –– Ethan Stark 7 pass from Chris Belling (run failed) 
Second quarter 
B –– Allen Jevning 15 run (David Saxum kick) 
B –– Mitch Rahn 2 run (Saxum kick) 
Third quarter 
S –– Jake Lieberg 16 pass from Belling (conversion failed) 
B –– Tristan Brecht 3 pass from Hanson Devine (Saxum kick) 
Fourth quarter 
S –– John Schmidt 3 run (Jordan Och kick) 
Individual statistics

Passing: S –– Belling 18-29-1 140; B –– Devine 5-10-1 47.
